---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="The Major Funding Landscape">
  <h1>I. The Major Funding Landscape (2025–2026)</h1>

  <p>
    The funding environment for AI in digital humanities has seen significant shifts over the past
    year, with both unprecedented investments and unexpected program cancellations reshaping the
    landscape for researchers and institutions.
  </p>

  <h2>Schmidt Sciences: HAVI Program</h2>

  <p>
    The <strong>Humanities and Artificial Intelligence (HAVI)</strong> program represents one of the
    most substantial private investments in AI-driven humanities research to date.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Total Investment</strong>: $11 million awarded to 23 interdisciplinary teams in December 2025</li>
    <li><strong>Next Deadline</strong>: March 13, 2026</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The HAVI program specifically targets projects that bring together humanists and AI researchers
    to develop new methodologies for cultural analysis, text processing, and archival work.
  </p>

  <h2>National Endowment for the Humanities (NEH)</h2>

  <p>
    The NEH has traditionally been a cornerstone funder for digital humanities initiatives in the
    United States, though recent changes have created uncertainty in the field.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Activity</strong>: Awarded $22.6 million for 219 projects in early 2025</li>
    <li><strong>Current Status</strong>: The Digital Humanities Advancement Grants program is cancelled for FY2026</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The cancellation of the DHAG program has prompted many institutions to seek alternative funding
    sources, including private foundations and international collaborations.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-10 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 rounded-r-lg not-prose">
    <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-2">Key Takeaway</h3>
    <p class="text-stone-700">
      While federal funding faces uncertainty, private foundations like Schmidt Sciences are
      stepping in with substantial investments, creating new opportunities for AI-humanities
      collaborations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <nav class="mt-12 flex justify-between not-prose">
    <a href={base} class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">&larr; Back to Home</a>
    <a href={`${base}transcription/`} class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Next: II. Manuscript Transcription &rarr;</a>
  </nav>
</Layout>
